1 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Preelection reports. (1) The commission shall compile a preelection
2 report for each judge relying on that judge's preelection evaluation. The preelection report may also be based
3 on further information the commission considers useful for purposes of judicial evaluation or self-improvement.
4 (2) The commission shall provide the preelection report to the evaluated judge, the Montana
5 supreme court, and the court administrator.
6 (3) (a) The commission may publish a partial preelection report for a judge whose appointment
7 date precludes the collection of complete preelection evaluation data. For a newly appointed judge, a
8 preelection report is considered partial when the preelection evaluation is missing a respondent group.
9 (b) The commission's webpage must identify each judge receiving a partial preelection report.
10 (4) Prior to a partial preelection report, the commission shall inform the court administrator of the
11 judges who will receive partial reports.
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Publication of judicial performance reports. (1) (a) The commission
14 shall provide each judge with the judge's reports in a timely manner. If a report is based on a preelection
15 evaluation, it must be provided at least 45 days before the last day on which the judge may file a declaration of
16 the judge's candidacy in the next election.
17 (b) Each report, together with the information collected for the report, must remain confidential
18 unless the judge who is the subject of the report files a declaration of candidacy in the ensuing election. In that
19 event, the report and the information collected for it become public record on the day following the last day on
20 which the judge may file a declaration of candidacy.
21 (2) The report must include:
22 (a) a summary of the results of the judicial performance survey and tabulations of the responses to
23 each question;
24 (b) information concerning any public discipline that a judge has received and is not subject to
25 restrictions on disclosure under Title 3, chapter 1, part 11;
26 (c) a narrative describing the judge’s performance with, at the option of the commission, an overall
27 score on a numerical scale from one to five;
